e about an order of magnitude larger than expected for heavy-ion\ncollisions, the system is substantially reheated and the lifetime of the quark\nphase might be extended.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Feb 2016 09:12:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Apr 2016 14:59:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-27"}
